news.title: Noida: YEIDA orders probe against officials for issuing false CCs
news.para: The Authority will also revoke the land allotted to the kiosks in sectors 32, 22D, 20 and 17A under various commercial department schemes. The completion certificates were issued to them between May and July.

news.title: SC dismisses ex-Goa judge’s plea to regain RERA post
news.para: The HC had also directed state govt to appoint retired district judge Vincent M D’Silva in Gauns’s place. The SC bench, comprising the Chief Justice and Justice Manoj Misra, heard Gauns.

news.title: Noida: Homebuyers' association oppose plan to pay full stamp duty during booking
news.para: Buyers expressed concern that their money would get stuck should the builder turned a defaulter and left the project midway. Earlier, buyers paid 10% of the flat cost as the booking amount and made an agreement with the builder on a 100-rupee stamp paper.

news.title: Builder can’t sell properties without basic amenities: Rajasthan HC
news.para: The court directed that urban development & housing department (UDH) must first issue a certificate to the developer or builder confirming whether the residential colony or society is suitable for habitation.

news.title: China's Shimao Group says creditors holding over 50% of debt support its restructuring plan
news.para: Shimao Group said in a filing late on Wednesday the amendments include controlling shareholders committing to not dispose of capital stock to below 20% of total voting power, and certain creditors being paid in mandatory convertible bonds as a fee.

news.title: Institutional investments in real estate rise 45% to $1.15 billion in Q2 FY25: Report
news.para: Among different assets class in the overall real estate market, the consultant noted that office segment attracted USD 616.3 million during the third quarter of this calendar year, a more than seven-fold jump from USD 79.1 million in the year-ago period.

news.title: Furnishka raises Rs 27 crore led by India Quotient
news.para: The new funds will be used to advance product design and development, strengthen manufacturing and supply chain capabilities, and expand to new geographies.

news.title: Madurai: Villagers around Tirunelveli oppose merger into civic body
news.para: Reddiyarpatti, Itteri, Munneerpallam, Nochikulam, Ramayanpatti, Thalaiyuthu, and Keelanatham villages were proposed to be brought under Tirunelveli municipal corporation as part of the plan to expand cities across the state.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto surge 3.3% in September 2024
news.para: Sales increased by 3.3% from August, the largest monthly advance since the 12.1% rise recorded in January, said the Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB).

news.title: Net absorption of office space rises 14% in Q2 FY25 across seven cities: Report
news.para: Real estate consultant JLL's latest data showed that the net absorption of office space stood at 12.16 million square feet in the third quarter of this fiscal year as against 10.69 million square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: Housing sales rise 5% to 87,108 units across eight cities in Q2 FY25: Report
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India on Thursday released its report 'India Real Estate' for the third quarter of 2024 calendar year through a webinar, showing a modest increase in housing sales in contrast to data provided by Anarock and PropEquity which reported drop in total sales during July-September across major cities.

news.title: Telangana HC grants bail to Nizampet municipal commissioner in HYDRAA case
news.para: The judge also agreed with the contention of the municipal commissioners association, which said that the TG b-PASS system had bypassed them and entrusted the task of granting or rejecting the building permissions to HMDA.

news.title: British land buys $585 million retail parks portfolio from Brookfield
news.para: The Broadgate owner has been doubling down on its investments in retail parks since 2021 as its core business of office-focused campuses still recovers from steep valuation declines in the aftermath of the Covid pandemic and the ill-timed UK mini-budget of 2022.

news.title: Rajasthan CM distributes land deeds to around 21,000 homeless tribal families
news.para: Earlier in the day, the chief minister visited the Khadi exhibition on the premises of the Rajasthan Khadi and Village Industries Board here where he garlanded the statue of Mahatma Gandhi on the occasion of his birth anniversary.

news.title: NRI scammed of Rs 3.6 crore by real estate firm in Hyderabad
news.para: The accused, after collecting the money, promised to get the property registered and then conned the businessman by making him wait at the sub-registrar's office and failing to turn up.

news.title: PMRDA demands micro plan for Pune's metro line three completion
news.para: With Central govt committing to the viability gap funding (an allocated percentage of funds for certain infrastructure projects), for the project, a progress report has to be submitted in the meeting, said officials.

news.title: Coimbatore civic body proposes merger to expand administrative area
news.para: The corporation has sent a proposal to the state govt to merge a municipality, four town panchayats and 11 village panchayats with it, taking its administrative area to 438.54 square kilometres (sqkm) from the current 257.04sqkm.

news.title: FrontView REIT raises $250.8 million in IPO
news.para: The Dallas, Texas-based company's shares opened at $18.25, below the initial public offering price of $19 apiece. It sold 13.2 million shares in the IPO, raising $250.8 million.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance plans to raise upto Rs 3,000 crore from retail investors
news.para: IIFL Home Finance plans its first retail fundraise in three years to diversify its liabilities. Filing a draft prospectus to raise up to Rs 3,000 crore, it aims for an initial fundraise of Rs 300-500 crore this quarter.
